# Copy to `.env.local` for local development.

# Admin (required for /admin)
ADMIN_PASSWORD=change-me
SESSION_SECRET=change-me-please-16chars-min

# Optional: whole-site password before launch. When set (non-empty), visitors must unlock at /site-gate.
# Uses the same SESSION_SECRET to sign the preview cookie. Remove or blank this variable when you go public.
# SITE_GATE_PASSWORD=

# --- Production (Vercel): hosted database (recommended) ---
# Vercel’s serverless filesystem is not a safe place for a writable SQLite file. Use Turso (libSQL, SQLite-compatible):
# 1) Install Turso CLI, create a DB, import your local file: https://docs.turso.tech/cli/db/import
# 2) In Vercel → Project → Settings → Environment Variables, add both (Production + Preview as needed):
# TURSO_DATABASE_URL=libsql://....turso.io
# TURSO_AUTH_TOKEN=...
# 3) When these are set, the app uses Turso; locally without them it uses ./data/site.db
# TURSO_DATABASE_URL=
# TURSO_AUTH_TOKEN=
# If Turso shows "no such table: series", run once (with same env): npm run db:ensure-turso
# Or import your local data/site.db into Turso for schema + rows: https://docs.turso.tech/cli/db/import
# Vercel: `npm run build` runs `prebuild` first — if TURSO_* are set for the build, tables are created automatically.

# Notes
# - Local SQLite path: `website/data/site.db` (when Turso env vars are unset)
# - After installing dependencies: `npm run db:push` (or `npm run db:ensure-home` for home CMS tables only)
# - Backup local DB before import: `npm run db:backup`
# - Run `npm run seed` only against the local file DB (unset TURSO_* in that shell)
